Additional Information:

Project: EcoSat Monitor - Urban Sustainability Dashboard
Author: Elizabeth Díaz Familia
Website: https://lizzy0981.github.io
Email: lizzyfamilia@gmail.com
Repository: https://github.com/Lizzy0981/ecosat-monitor

This project represents a professional implementation of environmental monitoring 
through advanced data science applications with real-time satellite data integration.

The technologies and methodologies implemented in this software are based on 
established environmental science and data analysis principles:

- NASA Earth Imagery API: Official satellite data from Landsat missions
- OpenWeatherMap Air Pollution API: Real-time air quality measurements
- NOAA Climate Data API: Historical and current climate information
- ESA Copernicus Atmosphere API: European satellite atmospheric data
- Chart.js: Professional data visualization library
- Leaflet: Open-source interactive mapping library
- Progressive Web App (PWA): Modern web application standards
- IndexedDB: Browser-based offline storage for data persistence

Educational Use:
This software is particularly suited for educational purposes in:
- Environmental science and sustainability studies
- Data science and environmental data analysis
- Web development and progressive web applications
- Geographic Information Systems (GIS) and satellite data
- User interface design for scientific applications
- Real-time data visualization and dashboard development

Environmental Impact:
This application promotes environmental awareness by:
- Providing accessible environmental data visualization
- Encouraging monitoring of air quality and climate metrics
- Gamifying environmental consciousness and education
- Supporting offline functionality to reduce data usage
- Demonstrating sustainable web development practices

Commercial Use:
While this software is free for commercial use under the MIT license, 
attribution to the original author is appreciated but not required.
The application integrates with publicly available APIs that may have
their own terms of service and usage limitations.

API Usage Disclaimer:
This application utilizes third-party APIs for environmental data:
- NASA APIs are provided under their open data policy
- OpenWeatherMap has free tier limitations (60 calls/minute)
- NOAA data is publicly available for non-commercial use
- Users should review individual API terms for commercial applications

Contributing:
Contributions, issues, and feature requests are welcome. Please refer to 
the project repository for contribution guidelines. Special consideration
is given to contributions that:
- Improve environmental data accuracy or sources
- Enhance accessibility and user experience
- Add support for additional environmental metrics
- Improve offline functionality and data synchronization

Disclaimer:
This software is designed for educational, research, and general environmental
monitoring purposes. While it uses official data sources, it should not be
used as the sole basis for critical environmental or safety decisions.
For professional environmental monitoring, emergency situations, or 
regulatory compliance, please consult certified environmental monitoring
systems and official governmental sources.

Data Privacy:
This application processes environmental data and user preferences locally
when possible. No personal environmental data is transmitted to third parties
beyond the necessary API calls for public environmental information.
User achievement and preference data is stored locally using browser storage.

